Leza Davies had a boob job to boost her confidence . 
  She thought breast feeding had left her breasts saggy and thought they were too big . 
  In 2012 she knocked her breast implant on a door frame and found a pea-sized lump . 
  She went to her GP and tests revealed the lump was cancerous . 
  Mother-of-three was told treatment would leave her infertile . 
  She had chemotherapy and radiotherapy and is now in remission . 
  She says her implants saved her life because she didn't regularly check for lumps . 
 